'''Grant Mossop''' (1948 - 7 October 2005<ref>{{cite journal|year=2005|title=Memorials: Grant Dilworth Mossop (1948-2005)|journal=Bulletin of Canadian Petroleum Geology|volume=53|issue=4|pages=500–501|url=http://bcpg.geoscienceworld.org/content/53/4/500.extract|doi=10.2113/53.4.500}}</ref>) was a geologist from Canada. He earned a B.Sc. in 1970 and an M.Sc. in 1971 from the [[University of Calgary]] followed by a Ph.D. in geology from the [[University of London]]. He served as the Director of the [[Institute of Sedimentary and Petroleum Geology, Geological Survey of Canada Calgary]]. A graduate scholarship in his name was established in 2009.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.ucalgary.ca/news/utoday/april15-09/mossop|title=Faces of Philanthropy|date=15 April 2009|work=UToday|publisher=[[University of Calgary]]|accessdate=17 March 2014}}</ref>
He was awarded the [[Ambrose Medal]] of the [[Geological Association of Canada]] in 1995. <ref> {{cite web|url= http://www.gac.ca/wp/?page_id=2066| title=Past Recipients| publisher= Geological Association of Canada|accessdate = 13 July 2015}} </ref>
