{{Infobox scientist | name = Leopoldo García-Colín Scherer | image = <!--(filename only)--> | image_size = | alt = | caption = | birth_date = {{Birth date and age|1930|11|27|df=y}} | birth_place = [[Mexico City, Mexico]]<ref name="colnac">{{cite web|title=Leopoldo García-Colín|url=http://www.colegionacional.org.mx/SACSCMS/XStatic/colegionacional/template/content.aspx?se=vida&te=detallemiembro&mi=120|publisher=[[Colegio Nacional (Mexico)|El Colegio Nacional]]|accessdate=27 December 2010|language=Spanish|year=2007|deadurl=yes|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110716204545/http://www.colegionacional.org.mx/SACSCMS/XStatic/colegionacional/template/content.aspx?se=vida&te=detallemiembro&mi=120|archivedate=16 July 2011|df=}}</ref> | death_date = {{Death date and age|2012|10|08|1930|11|27}}<ref name=obit>{{cite web|url=http://www.eluniversal.com.mx/cultura/70026.html |title=Cultura - Muere Leopoldo García-Colín, investigador mexicano |publisher=El Universal |date=2012-10-10 |accessdate=2012-10-14}}</ref> | death_place = Mexico City | nationality = Mexican | fields = Thermodynamics. Statistical Mechanics, mainly out of equilibrium | workplaces = [[Cinvestav]], [[Autonomous University of Puebla]], [[Metropolitan Autonomous University]]<ref name="rdu">{{cite news|title=Semblanza de Semblanza de Leopoldo García-Colín Scherer|url=http://www.revista.unam.mx/vol.2/num2/sembla1/|accessdate=27 December 2010|newspaper=Revista Digital Universitaria|date=30 June 2001|agency=[[Universidad Nacional Autónoma de México]]|language=Spanish}}, [[School of Physics and Mathematics, IPN]]{{cite web|url=http://www.colegionacional.org.mx/SACSCMS/XStatic/colegionacional/template/content.aspx?se=vida&te=detallemiembro&mi=120|title=Leopoldo García-Colín|author=<!--Not stated-->|website=http://www.colegionacional.org.mx|publisher=Colegio Nacional|access-date=5 December 2017|deadurl=yes|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110716204545/http://www.colegionacional.org.mx/SACSCMS/XStatic/colegionacional/template/content.aspx?se=vida&te=detallemiembro&mi=120|archivedate=16 July 2011|df=}}</ref> | alma_mater = [[National Autonomous University of Mexico]] (UNAM), [[University of Maryland, College Park]].<ref name="rdu" /> | doctoral_advisor = [[Elliott Waters Montroll]]<ref name="rdu" /> | academic_advisors = [[Marcos Moshinsky]], Alejandro Medina<ref name="rdu" /> | notable_students = | known_for = | influences = | influenced = | awards = [[National Prize for Arts and Sciences]] (Mexico, 1988) | footnotes = }}
'''Leopoldo García-Colín Scherer''' (born 27 November 1930 in [[Mexico City]], died 8 October 2012 in [[Mexico City]]) was a [[Mexico|Mexican]] scientist specialized in [[Thermodynamics]] and [[Statistical Mechanics]] who received the [[National Prize for Arts and Sciences]] in 1988.<ref name=obit/>
He was a member of [[Colegio Nacional (Mexico)|The National College]], a former president of the Mexican Society of Physics (''SMF'', 1972–1973) and has received honorary degrees from several universities, including the [[National Autonomous University of Mexico]] (UNAM) and the [[Metropolitan Autonomous University]] (UAM).<ref name="uam">{{cite web|title=Profesores distinguidos|url=http://cbi.izt.uam.mx/transform.php?xml=profesores_distinguidos|publisher=[[Universidad Autónoma Metropolitana]]|accessdate=27 December 2010|language=Spanish|deadurl=yes|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110722230252/http://cbi.izt.uam.mx/transform.php?xml=profesores_distinguidos|archivedate=22 July 2011|df=}}</ref>
== Biographical sketch ==
He obtained a [[Chemistry]] degree at [[Universidad Nacional Autónoma de México]] (UNAM) in 1953. The Ph.D. in [[Physics]] at the [[University of Maryland]] in 1959. He was professor at [[Benemérita Universidad Autónoma de Puebla]] from 1960 to 1963, and at [[Facultad de Ciencias de la UNAM|Facultad de Ciencias]] in UNAM from 1967 to 1984. Later, he participated in research at the [[Centro Nuclear de Salazar]], a Nuclear center in Mexico; assistant director of Basic Investigation of Processes at [[Instituto Mexicano del Petróleo]] from 1967 to 1974, professor at Instituto de Investigaciones de Materiales in UNAM during the period from 1984 to 1988. At the end of his career he had a tenure position at [[Universidad Autónoma Metropolitana]] at [[Iztapalapa]]. He was elected to [[El Colegio Nacional (Mexico)|El Colegio Nacional]] in September 12, 1977. He was member of the [[Sistema Nacional de Investigadores]] with the highest level, III, since 1988. He received a honris causa Ph. D from the National University of Mexico in April, 2007.
