The '''Ramesside star clocks''' are ancient Egyptian [[star clock]]s appearing on the ceilings of several royal tombs of the [[Ramesside period]]. Two sets of star clocks appear on the tomb [[Ramesses VII]] and [[Ramesses IX]].<ref name="Clagett">{{cite book | author=Marshall Clagett| title =Ancient Egyptian Science: Calendars, clocks, and astronomy| publisher =[[American Philosophical Society]]| year =1989| page =59| isbn =0871692147}}</ref> Although all of the sets are corrupt to some degree, a prototype clock can be reconstructed from them.<ref name="Clagett"/>
